          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USALAS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at the",
                "spallation neutron source at LANSCE Weapons Neutron",
                "Research (WNR) facility, driven by 800-MeV linear",
                "proton accelerator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-235",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.9991
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 235U target consisted of a",
                "deposit of 235U(F)4 on a thin carbon backing. The",
                "thickness of the 235U was 175.5 mu-g/cm2 and the",
                "backing thickness was 100 mu-g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BAF2"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Gamma rays were detected by DANCE - a 4Pi",
                "calorimetric gamma-ray detector. It consists of 160",
                "BaF2 crystals, each about 0.75 l in volume and 15 cm",
                "long. The face of each crystal is 17 cm from the",
                "sample center.The sample is surrounded by a 6 cm thick",
                "6LiH sphere to attenuate neutrons scattered from the",
                "sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time of flight was used to determine energy",
                "of incident neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "Spallation reaction of tungsten target by 800",
                "MeV protons was used as neutron source. A water",
                "moderator shapes the neutron spectrum. The beam spot",
                "at the sample location was about 1 cm in diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A composite flux was obtained by normalizing the flux",
                "from 235U(n,f) to that from 6Li(n,t) over the region",
                "from 3 to 10 keV. Data obtained using different monitor",
                "reactions are splitted in subs 2 and 3",
                "Cross section was normalized to resonance cross section",
                "calculated using parameters from ENDF/B-VII evaluation.",
                "Only s-wave resonances at 80.75,145.67 and 165.30 eV",
                "were used."
              ]
            }
          ],
